The engrossed copy of the Declaration renders the &quot;u&quot; in United States in small case, i.e. &quot;united States&quot;, one of several variations in capitalization and punctuation that historians Boyd and Becker believed to be of no significance; Boyd, Evolution, 25&lt;U+2013&gt;26. In his notes and Rough Draft, Jefferson capitalized variously as &quot;United states&quot; (Boyd, Papers of Jefferson, 1:315) and &quot;United States&quot; (ibid., 1:427).â©
